## Acquisition Metrics

### New Users

- **Definition**: [Count of users who completed signup on a given date. Specify what "completed signup" means -- email verified? First login? Payment?]
- **Formula**: `COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) WHERE signup_date = [date] AND [conditions]`
- **Data source**: `[schema].[table]`
- **Refresh frequency**: [Daily / Hourly / Real-time]
- **Owner**: [Name]
- **Dashboard**: [Link]

### Cost Per Acquisition (CPA)

- **Definition**: [Total marketing spend divided by new paying users in the period]
- **Formula**: `SUM(marketing_spend) / COUNT(new_paying_users)`
- **Data source**: [Marketing platform + payment system]
- **Refresh frequency**: [Weekly]
- **Owner**: [Name]
- **Dashboard**: [Link]

### [Additional Acquisition Metric]

- **Definition**: [Precise definition]
- **Formula**: [SQL or calculation]
- **Data source**: [Table]
- **Owner**: [Name]

## Activation Metrics

### Activation Rate

- **Definition**: [Percentage of new users who complete the activation criteria within X days of signup. Define activation criteria precisely.]
- **Formula**: `COUNT(activated_users) / COUNT(new_users) * 100`
- **Data source**: `[schema].[table]`
- **Refresh frequency**: [Daily]
- **Owner**: [Name]
- **Dashboard**: [Link]
- **Activation criteria**: [List the specific actions that qualify a user as "activated"]

### Time to Value

- **Definition**: [Median time from signup to first meaningful action. Define "meaningful action" precisely.]
- **Formula**: `MEDIAN(first_value_event_timestamp - signup_timestamp)`
- **Data source**: `[schema].[events_table]`
- **Owner**: [Name]

## Engagement Metrics

### Monthly Active Users (MAU)

- **Definition**: [Count of unique users who performed at least one qualifying action in the last 30 days. Define "qualifying action".]
- **Formula**: `COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) WHERE last_action_date >= DATEADD(day, -30, CURRENT_DATE)`
- **Data source**: `[schema].[table]`
- **Refresh frequency**: [Daily]
- **Owner**: [Name]
- **Dashboard**: [Link]

### Daily Active Users (DAU)

- **Definition**: [Count of unique users who performed at least one qualifying action on a given day]
- **Formula**: `COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) WHERE action_date = [date]`
- **Data source**: `[schema].[table]`
- **Owner**: [Name]

### DAU/MAU Ratio (Stickiness)

- **Definition**: [Ratio of daily to monthly active users. Higher = stickier product.]
- **Formula**: `DAU / MAU`
- **Target**: [X% -- note: 20%+ is considered good for most SaaS]
- **Owner**: [Name]

### [Feature-Specific Engagement]

- **Definition**: [Adoption rate or usage frequency for your most important feature]
- **Formula**: [SQL or calculation]
- **Data source**: [Table]
- **Owner**: [Name]

## Retention Metrics

### Monthly Churn Rate

- **Definition**: [Percentage of paying users at the start of the month who are no longer paying at the end. Specify: does a paused subscription count as churned? What about downgrades?]
- **Formula**: `COUNT(churned_users_in_month) / COUNT(active_users_at_month_start) * 100`
- **Data source**: `[schema].[table]`
- **Refresh frequency**: [Monthly, calculated on 1st of each month]
- **Owner**: [Name]
- **Dashboard**: [Link]
- **Caveats**: [Any edge cases in your churn definition -- refunds, plan changes, grace periods]

### Net Revenue Retention (NRR)

- **Definition**: [Revenue from existing customers this period vs. same cohort last period. Includes expansion, contraction, and churn.]
- **Formula**: `(Starting MRR + Expansion - Contraction - Churn) / Starting MRR * 100`
- **Data source**: [Billing system]
- **Owner**: [Name]
- **Target**: [X% -- note: 100%+ means you're growing from existing customers]

### Cohort Retention

- **Definition**: [Percentage of a signup cohort still active after N days/months]
- **Cohort definition**: [What groups users into a cohort -- signup week? signup month?]
- **Data source**: `[schema].[table]`
- **Standard intervals**: [Day 1, Day 7, Day 30, Month 3, Month 6, Month 12]
- **Owner**: [Name]

## Revenue Metrics

### Monthly Recurring Revenue (MRR)

- **Definition**: [Sum of all recurring revenue normalized to a monthly amount. Exclude one-time charges, include discounts.]
- **Formula**: `SUM(monthly_plan_amount) for all active subscriptions`
- **Data source**: `[schema].[table]`
- **Refresh frequency**: [Daily]
- **Owner**: [Name]
- **Dashboard**: [Link]

### Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR)

- **Definition**: [MRR * 12. Simple annualization of current MRR.]
- **Formula**: `MRR * 12`
- **Owner**: [Name]

### Average Revenue Per User (ARPU)

- **Definition**: [MRR divided by active paying users]
- **Formula**: `MRR / COUNT(active_paying_users)`
- **Data source**: `[schema].[table]`
- **Owner**: [Name]

### Lifetime Value (LTV)

- **Definition**: [Average revenue per user divided by monthly churn rate. Or use your preferred calculation method.]
- **Formula**: `ARPU / monthly_churn_rate`
- **Data source**: [Derived metric]
- **Owner**: [Name]
- **Caveats**: [LTV estimates are sensitive to churn assumptions. State your methodology.]

### LTV:CAC Ratio

- **Definition**: [Lifetime value divided by customer acquisition cost]
- **Formula**: `LTV / CPA`
- **Target**: [3:1 or higher]
- **Owner**: [Name]

