## Common Queries

### Active users for a date range

```sql
-- Replace with your actual query
SELECT
    date_trunc('day', activity_date) as day,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) as active_users
FROM [schema].[activity_table]
WHERE activity_date BETWEEN '[start_date]' AND '[end_date]'
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 1;
```

### MRR trend

```sql
-- Replace with your actual query
SELECT
    date_trunc('month', report_date) as month,
    SUM(mrr_amount) as total_mrr
FROM [schema].[subscription_table]
WHERE status = 'active'
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 1;
```

### Cohort retention

```sql
-- Replace with your actual query
SELECT
    cohort_month,
    months_since_signup,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) as retained_users,
    retained_users / cohort_size * 100 as retention_pct
FROM [schema].[cohort_view]
GROUP BY 1, 2
ORDER BY 1, 2;
```
